pulsar

Class PulsarProcessWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • pulsar.PulsarProcessWrapper

  • public class PulsarProcessWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
    It seems that if a class has an abstract method, Kawa cannot call the method unless its user explicitly specifies the type of the variable which stores the instance of the class. The intension of this class is simply wrap the abstract class by a concrete class in order to avoid the problem. (Sat, 19 Oct 2019 01:16:47 +0900)
